-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate billing events to one per subscription + event_month (latest event)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/intermediate/int_subscription_details.sql
```sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with user, company, and plan details
WITH subs AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
),
users AS (
    SELECT
        u.user_id,
        u.company_id
    FROM {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
),
companies AS (
    SELECT
        c.company_id,
        c.industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
),
plans AS (
    SELECT
        p.plan_id,
        p.tier,
        p.monthly_price
    FROM {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
),
joined AS (
    SELECT
        subs.subscription_id,
        subs.user_id,
        subs.started_at,
        subs.ended_at,
        COALESCE(plans.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(companies.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        plans.monthly_price
    FROM subs
    LEFT JOIN users
        ON users.user_id = subs.user_id
    LEFT JOIN companies
        ON companies.company_id = users.company_id
    LEFT JOIN plans
        ON plans.plan_id = subs.plan_id
)
SELECT * FROM joined
```

-- Determine active subscriptions per month
WITH sub_details AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        user_id,
        started_at,
        ended_at,
        tier,
        industry,
        monthly_price
    FROM {{ ref('int_subscription_details') }}
),
billing AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }}
),
matched AS (
    SELECT
        billing.event_month,
        sub_details.subscription_id,
        sub_details.user_id,
        sub_details.tier,
        sub_details.industry,
        sub_details.monthly_price
    FROM billing
    LEFT JOIN sub_details
        ON sub_details.subscription_id = billing.subscription_id
)
SELECT * FROM matched

-- models/marts/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics: active count, MRR, unique users by tier and industry
WITH monthly_subs AS (
    SELECT
        event_month,
        subscription_id,
        user_id,
        tier,
        industry,
        monthly_price
    FROM {{ ref('int_monthly_subscriptions') }}
)
SELECT
    monthly_subs.event_month AS month,
    COALESCE(monthly_subs.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
    COALESCE(monthly_subs.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT monthly_subs.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    COALESCE(SUM(monthly_subs.monthly_price), 0) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT monthly_subs.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM monthly_subs
GROUP BY
    monthly_subs.event_month,
    COALESCE(monthly_subs.tier, '(unknown)'),
    COALESCE(monthly_subs.industry, '(unknown)')
ORDER BY month ASC, tier ASC, industry ASC
